<br>
If your taking a lof of dirt naps in Oasis.. thats a good indicator that you may be too low for it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Paradigm</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(4/14/01 1:01:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Not really</span><hr size=1> I went to oasis at 12 and didn't leave till 18 to do gargs in oot.  The caimans are fair game to a mage and his water pet. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usarfa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sarfa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#333333>(4/14/01 8:54:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Not really</span><hr size=1> Why the hell does everyone hunt in Oasis??? It sucks! try running up and down the beach looking for a caimen at level 12 and not have it KSed before you kill it.   Pack your bags and go to Overthere.  I know what you are all going to start yelling now &quot;OT isn't safe until post 16&quot; WRONG.  Get a map, find the canyon where the skorpikis spawns.  Now go walk towards the Warsliks Woods side of the canyon.  Now start conning things.  You will see BLUE, even, yellow, and the occasional red mobs.  Set up camp by the canyon and start pulling sarnak youths, sabertooths cats and succulants(forgot the name of the low succulants)  Most of them will be even to blue lvl range from 10-13.  The absolute best XP anywhere I have ever found and very doable solo as a mage.  You can go there at 12 and stay till 22 then go to treants or Lake of Ill Omen. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usarfa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sarfa</A> at: 4/14/01 2:55:27 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ustrongarmluclin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>strongarm luclin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(4/16/01 12:37:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Not really</span><hr size=1> Personaly I dislike the hole FP area, mostly due to how disenchanting it can get with the massive crowed. People dont seem as friendly either, at 12 I hunted in SRo, killing snakes and spiders. Good EXP, I carried a tailors bag for the massive amount of silks I got. And at 16 I moved to EK were I went to 22 on Crags. Now I am looking for a new place to hunt. Im trying not to go to RoK, or at least follow the same zone leveling path my Druid is. So any suggestions other then Lake of Ill Omen!<br>
